DataElement.preferredDefinition: The spatial outline of an object as described by the configuration of straight or curved lines.:Having, relating to, or consisting of more than one individual, element, part, or other component; manifold. (dictionary.com):A mark that is long relative to its width; a length (straight or curved) without breadth or thickness; the trace of a moving point._Doughnut-shaped object or surface generated by rotating a circle around an axis that does not intersect the circle; any object that resembles a ring.:An indicator that can be set or unset in order to signal whether a particular condition is true._Values of two-valued logic.
